1
00:00:18,120 --> 00:00:18,640
Hello.

2
00:00:19,559 --> 00:00:20,160
Bro Li.

3
00:00:20,600 --> 00:00:22,440
I know who gave Ruolan the knockout drug.

4
00:00:22,920 --> 00:00:24,239
Get to Benevolence Clinic right now.

5
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:25,399
Got it.

6
00:01:21,760 --> 00:01:22,239
Hey.

7
00:01:33,560 --> 00:01:34,200
Ruolan's friend.

8
00:01:34,200 --> 00:01:35,239
Xing Mingliang, right?

9
00:01:35,560 --> 00:01:36,400
Stop pretending.

10
00:01:36,799 --> 00:01:37,840
There's no one else here.

11
00:01:39,400 --> 00:01:40,200
Let's talk.

12
00:01:42,959 --> 00:01:44,040
It's about time we talked.

13
00:01:44,879 --> 00:01:45,719
Come to my office.

14
00:02:01,920 --> 00:02:02,680
Xing Mingliang!

15
00:02:03,439 --> 00:02:04,120
Xing Mingliang!

16
00:02:06,359 --> 00:02:07,040
Xing Mingliang!

17
00:02:15,199 --> 00:02:15,800
Mingliang!

18
00:02:18,840 --> 00:02:19,560
Let go!

19
00:02:20,400 --> 00:02:21,159
What are you doing?

20
00:02:21,319 --> 00:02:22,800
Are you crazy? Get down!

21
00:02:23,520 --> 00:02:24,520
He's trying to kill me!

22
00:02:24,840 --> 00:02:25,960
He's trying to kill me!

23
00:02:26,759 --> 00:02:27,319
Dr. Meng!

24
00:02:27,960 --> 00:02:28,599
Dr. Meng!

25
00:02:29,360 --> 00:02:30,479
He's trying to kill me, bro!

26
00:02:30,479 --> 00:02:31,159
Dr. Meng!

27
00:02:31,560 --> 00:02:32,479
He's trying to kill me!

28
00:02:34,159 --> 00:02:36,280
Boss, what on earth happened?

29
00:02:36,919 --> 00:02:38,240
You've asked me almost twenty times.

30
00:02:42,680 --> 00:02:44,360
Can't you just tell me properly, once?

31
00:02:44,560 --> 00:02:46,120
If I knew, wouldn't I have told you?

32
00:02:53,080 --> 00:02:54,479
Enough, stop pacing.

33
00:02:54,560 --> 00:02:55,759
You'll wear through your soles.

34
00:02:56,159 --> 00:02:58,159
Xing Mingliang is Chief Xing's son.

35
00:02:58,479 --> 00:02:59,680
If anything happens to him...

36
00:02:59,800 --> 00:03:01,960
And the thing is, you were right there.

37
00:03:03,280 --> 00:03:04,039
I'm saying this for your own good.

38
00:03:04,039 --> 00:03:04,879
Don't get annoyed with me.

39
00:03:09,360 --> 00:03:10,280
What the hell happened?

40
00:03:12,599 --> 00:03:13,599
Say something!

41
00:03:14,199 --> 00:03:14,879
Lost your voice?

42
00:03:16,639 --> 00:03:18,360
Captain Wang, I've been asking forever.

43
00:03:18,639 --> 00:03:19,879
I couldn't make sense of it either.

44
00:03:22,280 --> 00:03:23,039
How is he?

45
00:03:23,280 --> 00:03:24,639
Aside from significant blood loss,

46
00:03:24,639 --> 00:03:25,360
which left him weak,

47
00:03:25,360 --> 00:03:26,560
there's nothing seriously wrong.

48
00:03:26,840 --> 00:03:28,879
The wound is on the lower left abdomen.

49
00:03:29,639 --> 00:03:30,680
The depth of the blade's penetration

50
00:03:31,080 --> 00:03:32,400
narrowly missed any vital organs.

51
00:03:32,960 --> 00:03:35,319
So the patient is quite lucky.

52
00:03:35,479 --> 00:03:36,159
Thank you.

53
00:03:38,840 --> 00:03:40,000
You keep your mouth shut in there.

54
00:03:51,120 --> 00:03:51,759
Liangliang.

55
00:03:53,479 --> 00:03:54,560
Uncle Wang, how are you feeling?

56
00:03:54,680 --> 00:03:56,159
It hurts, it hurts.

57
00:03:57,520 --> 00:03:58,280
What happened?

58
00:04:00,479 --> 00:04:01,840
It's none of your business.

59
00:04:02,520 --> 00:04:04,599
Liangliang, is that how you talk to your dad?

60
00:04:04,800 --> 00:04:05,919
Your dad is worried sick about you.

61
00:04:05,919 --> 00:04:06,719
I can't tell.

62
00:04:08,840 --> 00:04:10,439
He doesn't care about me.

63
00:04:12,520 --> 00:04:14,000
You'd be glad if I were dead.

64
00:04:15,560 --> 00:04:16,959
If you can't speak properly,

65
00:04:17,199 --> 00:04:17,920
once you're feeling better,

66
00:04:18,399 --> 00:04:19,480
we'll talk in the interrogation room.

67
00:04:20,560 --> 00:04:21,199
Chief Xing.

68
00:04:21,800 --> 00:04:23,680
You know your own son's temper.

69
00:04:24,120 --> 00:04:26,120
Liangliang, can you speak civilly?

70
00:04:28,959 --> 00:04:30,720
Tell us what happened tonight.

71
00:04:36,480 --> 00:04:37,399
The truth is,

72
00:04:38,680 --> 00:04:40,519
the one stalking and spying on Ruolan,

73
00:04:41,639 --> 00:04:42,959
the one who injected her with the knockout drug

74
00:04:43,240 --> 00:04:44,160
and assaulted her,

75
00:04:46,560 --> 00:04:47,680
is Meng Yu.

76
00:04:50,600 --> 00:04:51,399
How do you know?

77
00:04:52,160 --> 00:04:53,199
How do I know?

78
00:04:53,959 --> 00:04:55,720
That night when I was struggling with him,

79
00:04:56,680 --> 00:04:58,879
I smelled disinfectant on him.

80
00:04:59,279 --> 00:05:01,240
Today, while I was helping Ruolan move,

81
00:05:01,480 --> 00:05:03,160
I saw someone spying from under a tree.

82
00:05:03,439 --> 00:05:04,560
So I followed him.

83
00:05:05,040 --> 00:05:07,000
I followed him to Benevolence Clinic.

84
00:05:08,079 --> 00:05:09,120
Why didn't you call the police?

85
00:05:09,759 --> 00:05:10,839
Call the police for what?

86
00:05:12,079 --> 00:05:13,000
I wasn't even sure.

87
00:05:13,800 --> 00:05:15,240
I had to confirm it myself.

88
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:16,519
Right.

89
00:05:16,920 --> 00:05:18,560
I even called Bro Li.

90
00:05:19,040 --> 00:05:20,199
After I told him,

91
00:05:20,439 --> 00:05:21,639
I went straight to find Meng Yu.

92
00:05:24,040 --> 00:05:25,439
At 11:35 PM,

93
00:05:25,839 --> 00:05:27,519
Mingliang did call me.

94
00:05:27,920 --> 00:05:29,040
He told me to come to Benevolence Clinic.

95
00:05:33,959 --> 00:05:34,959
Why did you start fighting?

96
00:05:35,879 --> 00:05:36,639
A fight?

97
00:05:37,160 --> 00:05:39,360
You think this was just a fight?

98
00:05:39,959 --> 00:05:41,560
He, he, he...

99
00:05:41,720 --> 00:05:42,879
He tried to kill me.

100
00:05:43,720 --> 00:05:45,079
I had to act in self-defense.

101
00:05:48,920 --> 00:05:49,920
I never imagined

102
00:05:51,399 --> 00:05:53,839
Ruolan was working for a demon all along.

103
00:05:57,240 --> 00:05:58,480
You really are clever.

104
00:05:59,600 --> 00:06:01,160
No wonder Ruolan likes you.

105
00:06:02,680 --> 00:06:03,680
If it weren't for you,

106
00:06:05,120 --> 00:06:06,439
Ruolan would've been mine long ago.

107
00:06:06,680 --> 00:06:08,319
What's your relationship with Ma Shijiang?

108
00:06:12,480 --> 00:06:14,360
We just share a common hobby.

109
00:06:15,800 --> 00:06:16,920
We both have

110
00:06:17,680 --> 00:06:19,399
slender and nimble hands.

111
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:22,000
Wearing the Red Gloves that women love,

112
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:23,040
to conquer women,

113
00:06:24,519 --> 00:06:25,959
brings the ultimate

114
00:06:27,199 --> 00:06:28,079
pleasure

115
00:06:28,839 --> 00:06:29,639
and satisfaction.

116
00:06:30,480 --> 00:06:31,279
Pervert!

117
00:06:35,720 --> 00:06:37,240
Do you really know what a pervert is?

118
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:39,319
It's nothing but a casual label

119
00:06:39,759 --> 00:06:42,480
that you so-called normal people slap

120
00:06:42,920 --> 00:06:44,560
on normal people like us.

121
00:06:45,720 --> 00:06:48,680
Don't you have hidden desires deep inside?

122
00:06:50,399 --> 00:06:52,680
You just keep them buried in your heart.

123
00:06:52,920 --> 00:06:53,720
But I,

124
00:06:55,279 --> 00:06:57,560
simply follow my own heart.

125
00:06:58,560 --> 00:07:00,879
You get satisfaction from hurting others.

126
00:07:01,879 --> 00:07:02,800
You're a pervert.

127
00:07:04,839 --> 00:07:06,480
You self-righteous people

128
00:07:08,240 --> 00:07:10,959
merely suppress those desires bound by

129
00:07:11,360 --> 00:07:12,079
so-called moral codes

130
00:07:12,959 --> 00:07:14,519
deep within your hearts.

131
00:07:14,600 --> 00:07:15,439
But I,

132
00:07:16,920 --> 00:07:19,079
simply tore off the hypocritical mask.

133
00:07:21,120 --> 00:07:22,560
You are absolutely absurd.

134
00:07:23,480 --> 00:07:25,079
You hurt defenseless women

135
00:07:25,519 --> 00:07:27,360
to flaunt that you're not a hypocrite.

136
00:07:29,199 --> 00:07:31,399
You call yourself a life-saving doctor?

137
00:07:34,600 --> 00:07:37,319
I'm merely testing the limits of human nature.

138
00:07:39,240 --> 00:07:40,600
Hey, you know what?

139
00:07:41,319 --> 00:07:43,040
When I stand at the operating table,

140
00:07:44,199 --> 00:07:47,319
seeing the bodies of despairing patients,

141
00:07:49,160 --> 00:07:50,480
I truly pity them.

142
00:07:52,439 --> 00:07:54,199
Their hearts are filled with

143
00:07:54,759 --> 00:07:55,519
fear

144
00:07:56,680 --> 00:07:57,759
and the will to survive.

145
00:07:58,560 --> 00:07:59,439
But I,

146
00:08:00,519 --> 00:08:02,199
possess the hands of God,

147
00:08:04,279 --> 00:08:06,319
easily controlling their life and death.

148
00:08:08,360 --> 00:08:09,639
What does that prove?

149
00:08:10,959 --> 00:08:12,279
It only proves

150
00:08:12,600 --> 00:08:14,959
that you are an utter and complete pervert.

151
00:08:26,160 --> 00:08:27,120
Scared now, aren't you?

152
00:08:27,399 --> 00:08:29,240
With just a flick of my hand,

153
00:08:30,600 --> 00:08:31,600
your life

154
00:08:33,039 --> 00:08:34,600
will vanish in the wind.

155
00:08:35,840 --> 00:08:37,120
I suggest you turn yourself in.

156
00:08:40,440 --> 00:08:41,600
Too bad the police

157
00:08:43,279 --> 00:08:45,519
won't find any evidence against me.

158
00:08:46,240 --> 00:08:47,320
I'm the witness.

159
00:08:48,399 --> 00:08:49,600
I've already told Captain Li.

160
00:08:50,559 --> 00:08:51,799
He's on his way here.

161
00:08:53,120 --> 00:08:54,080
You know what?

162
00:08:55,399 --> 00:08:56,399
Dead men

163
00:08:57,879 --> 00:08:59,279
tell no tales.

164
00:09:12,159 --> 00:09:13,240
I... I was so scared.

165
00:09:13,240 --> 00:09:15,159
He charged at me with a knife.

166
00:09:15,279 --> 00:09:16,879
So I looked around for something.

167
00:09:17,039 --> 00:09:18,639
In the motorcycle's tool box,

168
00:09:18,799 --> 00:09:20,559
I grabbed a hammer and went at him.

169
00:09:22,679 --> 00:09:23,399
Chief Xing.

170
00:09:24,399 --> 00:09:25,159
Captain Wang, Captain Li.

171
00:09:25,559 --> 00:09:27,720
Meng Yu suffered a severe brain injury.

172
00:09:27,919 --> 00:09:29,080
He'll likely end up in a vegetative state.

173
00:09:31,759 --> 00:09:32,840
Why did you hit him so hard?

174
00:09:34,440 --> 00:09:35,960
I told you, I was defending myself.

175
00:09:38,440 --> 00:09:39,720
Did you want me to die?

176
00:09:43,159 --> 00:09:43,879
Li Kaiyang.

177
00:09:46,080 --> 00:09:47,360
You've seen what happened here.

178
00:09:47,679 --> 00:09:48,519
I'm leaving this to you.

179
00:09:49,039 --> 00:09:50,320
Take him to the station once he's better.

180
00:09:50,519 --> 00:09:51,360
Interrogate him thoroughly.

181
00:09:51,519 --> 00:09:52,519
No favoritism, no bending the law.

182
00:09:52,720 --> 00:09:53,759
Or I won't let you off.

183
00:09:54,960 --> 00:09:55,840
Hey, Chief Xing.

184
00:09:57,240 --> 00:09:59,679
I just heard the kid's account of events.

185
00:09:59,960 --> 00:10:02,919
It basically counts as self-defense.

186
00:10:03,240 --> 00:10:04,519
No need to bring him to the station.

187
00:10:04,840 --> 00:10:06,840
Nonsense! You're the squad captain.

188
00:10:07,080 --> 00:10:08,399
You'd just take his word for it?

189
00:10:08,519 --> 00:10:09,120
Huh?

190
00:10:13,360 --> 00:10:14,519
Provide full medical care for Meng Yu.

191
00:10:14,759 --> 00:10:15,559
Per regulations,

192
00:10:15,879 --> 00:10:17,039
I need to recuse myself from this case.

193
00:10:25,759 --> 00:10:26,720
Hey, where are you going?

194
00:10:27,440 --> 00:10:28,919
Chief Xing told you to handle this.

195
00:10:30,120 --> 00:10:31,720
Didn't you just tell Chief Xing

196
00:10:32,519 --> 00:10:35,279
that Mingliang acted in self-defense?

197
00:10:35,480 --> 00:10:36,840
So shouldn't I go find evidence

198
00:10:36,840 --> 00:10:38,200
to prove that you're right?

199
00:10:38,559 --> 00:10:39,200
Hey, Li Kaiyang.

200
00:10:39,200 --> 00:10:40,279
What's gotten into you lately?

201
00:10:40,759 --> 00:10:41,799
Did you take the wrong pills or something?

202
00:10:42,440 --> 00:10:44,000
Every word out of your mouth is loaded.

203
00:10:44,519 --> 00:10:45,919
Keep me posted on Su Zhuang's condition.

204
00:10:46,120 --> 00:10:46,919
Yes, Captain Li.

205
00:11:02,879 --> 00:11:03,840
Why aren't the lights on?

206
00:11:04,399 --> 00:11:06,120
Captain Li, there's a wiring issue.

207
00:11:18,600 --> 00:11:19,200
Jiang Han.

208
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:20,679
Observe.

209
00:11:31,759 --> 00:11:32,559
What did you find?

210
00:11:34,360 --> 00:11:36,600
This blood must belong to Xing Mingliang.

211
00:11:36,840 --> 00:11:38,679
Judging from the blood splatter pattern,

212
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:40,679
he must have been running fast.

213
00:11:41,120 --> 00:11:42,879
And there are footprints in the blood.

214
00:11:43,240 --> 00:11:44,600
Meng Yu must have been chasing him.

215
00:11:45,360 --> 00:11:47,159
I've been to this place many times.

216
00:11:47,399 --> 00:11:48,919
I should be very familiar with it.

217
00:11:49,440 --> 00:11:50,480
But today, from the moment I walked in,

218
00:11:50,600 --> 00:11:52,039
I felt a strange unfamiliarity.

219
00:11:53,759 --> 00:11:54,519
Why?

220
00:11:56,360 --> 00:11:57,399
Day and night,

221
00:11:57,720 --> 00:11:58,679
memory and reality,

222
00:11:58,799 --> 00:12:00,480
all create perceptual biases in us.

223
00:12:01,240 --> 00:12:02,879
The key is the mental shift.

224
00:12:03,399 --> 00:12:05,039
Before, I came here as a patient.

225
00:12:05,159 --> 00:12:06,519
But today, I'm here to solve a case.

226
00:12:07,240 --> 00:12:08,480
Any subtle change

227
00:12:08,840 --> 00:12:10,120
can have an impact on things.

228
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:12,799
I see.

229
00:12:13,039 --> 00:12:15,320
So I must think like a true detective.

230
00:12:15,840 --> 00:12:17,879
Theory must be combined with practice.

231
00:12:18,879 --> 00:12:19,879
As a detective,

232
00:12:19,879 --> 00:12:21,120
you must trust your instincts,

233
00:12:21,120 --> 00:12:22,440
but never be controlled by them.

234
00:12:22,840 --> 00:12:23,559
Over time,

235
00:12:23,559 --> 00:12:25,320
You'll build your own case-solving system.

236
00:12:25,759 --> 00:12:26,879
A case-solving system?

237
00:12:27,240 --> 00:12:28,120
That sounds so impressive.

238
00:12:28,879 --> 00:12:30,799
Every detective has a case-solving system.

239
00:12:31,480 --> 00:12:33,200
Every time I enter a crime scene,

240
00:12:33,360 --> 00:12:35,000
I try to connect with the thoughts

241
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:35,799
in my own mind.

242
00:12:36,720 --> 00:12:37,679
Because these thoughts

243
00:12:37,879 --> 00:12:39,559
may carry some special significance.

244
00:12:40,120 --> 00:12:41,200
They're fleeting,

245
00:12:41,840 --> 00:12:43,000
and often easily overlooked.

246
00:12:44,399 --> 00:12:45,679
But if you can accurately capture

247
00:12:45,679 --> 00:12:46,840
that meaningful thought,

248
00:12:47,360 --> 00:12:48,399
it could very well lead us

249
00:12:48,399 --> 00:12:49,879
in the right direction to solve the case.

250
00:13:03,480 --> 00:13:04,120
Boss.

251
00:13:04,600 --> 00:13:05,200
Boss.

252
00:13:05,840 --> 00:13:06,679
What's wrong?

253
00:13:10,240 --> 00:13:12,919
If Meng Yu really meant to kill Mingliang,

254
00:13:13,440 --> 00:13:15,039
would he have hesitated while chasing him?

255
00:13:15,879 --> 00:13:16,960
Probably not, right?

256
00:13:20,240 --> 00:13:21,600
Are there no cameras here?

257
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:23,679
Outside, yes. Inside, no.

258
00:13:23,919 --> 00:13:25,039
For client privacy.

259
00:13:28,720 --> 00:13:29,360
Jiang Han.

260
00:13:29,720 --> 00:13:30,519
Call Lin Xue.

261
00:13:30,639 --> 00:13:32,039
Ask if Meng Yu's phone was on him.

262
00:13:32,159 --> 00:13:32,679
Got it.

263
00:13:43,440 --> 00:13:44,000
Boss.

264
00:13:44,279 --> 00:13:46,480
Lin Xue said Meng Yu's phone was on him.

265
00:13:46,720 --> 00:13:47,759
But the strange thing is,

266
00:13:47,759 --> 00:13:49,080
his phone looks brand new.

267
00:13:49,080 --> 00:13:50,240
There's nothing stored on it.

268
00:14:08,759 --> 00:14:09,879
Red Gloves.

269
00:14:10,279 --> 00:14:11,600
Why is it the Red Gloves again?

270
00:14:11,960 --> 00:14:13,639
I've been dreaming about them every night.

271
00:14:14,720 --> 00:14:17,240
Could Meng Yu be Ma Shijiang's accomplice?

272
00:14:18,480 --> 00:14:19,440
Xing Mingliang.

273
00:14:21,679 --> 00:14:22,799
Why are you back so late?

274
00:14:23,559 --> 00:14:24,159
Bro Li.

275
00:14:25,679 --> 00:14:26,679
What brings you here?

276
00:14:26,919 --> 00:14:28,840
Did something happen to Mingliang?

277
00:14:30,320 --> 00:14:31,120
Let's talk inside.

278
00:14:31,639 --> 00:14:33,000
Okay, come on in.

279
00:14:41,919 --> 00:14:44,159
He left Dr. Meng in a vegetative state?

280
00:14:44,679 --> 00:14:45,480
Sit down first.

281
00:14:51,159 --> 00:14:52,120
That's how it stands now.

282
00:14:52,320 --> 00:14:53,399
But whether he'll wake up

283
00:14:53,600 --> 00:14:55,200
depends on his ongoing treatment.

284
00:14:57,440 --> 00:14:58,919
How did it come to this?

285
00:15:00,120 --> 00:15:00,960
Ever since I...

286
00:15:04,080 --> 00:15:05,679
Everything has changed.

287
00:15:06,159 --> 00:15:07,600
You've been working for Meng Yu

288
00:15:08,039 --> 00:15:09,120
for over a year now, right?

289
00:15:13,320 --> 00:15:14,600
What do you think of him as a person?

290
00:15:17,919 --> 00:15:19,360
Dr. Meng is a really good person.

291
00:15:20,840 --> 00:15:22,000
Whether to his staff

292
00:15:22,559 --> 00:15:23,600
or to his patients,

293
00:15:24,600 --> 00:15:25,759
especially the patients,

294
00:15:26,159 --> 00:15:27,240
no matter what they do,

295
00:15:27,240 --> 00:15:28,159
or whether they have money,

296
00:15:28,320 --> 00:15:29,639
he treats everyone equally,

297
00:15:29,639 --> 00:15:30,600
with genuine care.

298
00:15:31,960 --> 00:15:33,240
Then think back carefully.

299
00:15:35,159 --> 00:15:36,320
In your daily interactions with him,

300
00:15:37,440 --> 00:15:38,759
did he ever act unusually?

301
00:15:44,360 --> 00:15:45,919
Dr. Meng is a very kind person.

302
00:15:47,840 --> 00:15:50,320
Big hospitals rejected many patients,

303
00:15:50,679 --> 00:15:52,360
but he would still treat them.

304
00:15:53,240 --> 00:15:53,879
And some patients,

305
00:15:53,879 --> 00:15:54,639
even without money,

306
00:15:54,639 --> 00:15:56,480
he would never turn them away.

307
00:15:58,120 --> 00:15:58,639
How could someone like that

308
00:15:58,639 --> 00:16:00,720
be a perverted stalker?

309
00:16:01,919 --> 00:16:03,919
Human psychology is extremely complex.

310
00:16:04,720 --> 00:16:07,000
Some who seem kind and outstanding

311
00:16:07,399 --> 00:16:08,000
may harbor inside

312
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:09,919
hidden emotions

313
00:16:09,919 --> 00:16:10,879
and psychological trauma.

314
00:16:11,639 --> 00:16:15,080
Once triggered by certain factors,

315
00:16:15,240 --> 00:16:17,759
it can lead to irrational behavior.

316
00:16:22,159 --> 00:16:22,759
But

317
00:16:23,919 --> 00:16:26,799
Dr. Meng is extremely even-tempered.

318
00:16:26,919 --> 00:16:28,480
I've been at the clinic for over a year,

319
00:16:28,759 --> 00:16:30,960
and I've never seen him lose his temper.

320
00:16:31,679 --> 00:16:32,919
Even with those

321
00:16:33,360 --> 00:16:34,639
who were being completely unreasonable,

322
00:16:34,639 --> 00:16:36,559
he still treated them with patience.

323
00:16:39,279 --> 00:16:40,559
Do you think Meng Yu likes you?

324
00:16:47,360 --> 00:16:47,840
Morning.

325
00:16:49,919 --> 00:16:52,080
Freshly brewed coffee, ready for you.

326
00:16:52,679 --> 00:16:53,639
Drink it while it's hot.

327
00:16:57,039 --> 00:16:58,840
Dr. Meng was indeed very nice to me.

328
00:17:00,519 --> 00:17:01,639
Thinking about it now,

329
00:17:02,919 --> 00:17:03,559
sometimes

330
00:17:03,559 --> 00:17:05,880
it did seem beyond ordinary coworkers.

331
00:17:09,720 --> 00:17:10,319
But

332
00:17:11,559 --> 00:17:12,920
my woman's intuition tells me

333
00:17:13,160 --> 00:17:15,640
he couldn't possibly be a pervert.

334
00:17:16,359 --> 00:17:17,279
What about Xing Mingliang?

335
00:17:18,759 --> 00:17:20,599
Mingliang treated me even better.

336
00:17:24,480 --> 00:17:25,839
He's such a kind person.

337
00:17:26,400 --> 00:17:27,880
How could he ever pick up a hammer?

338
00:17:31,599 --> 00:17:32,400
Impossible.

339
00:17:36,000 --> 00:17:37,079
I once worked a case

340
00:17:39,200 --> 00:17:40,400
where the suspect, on the outside,

341
00:17:41,359 --> 00:17:42,880
was seen as a good husband

342
00:17:44,039 --> 00:17:44,839
and a good father.

343
00:17:46,559 --> 00:17:48,039
He was diligent at work,

344
00:17:49,160 --> 00:17:50,880
and his neighbors spoke highly of him.

345
00:17:51,599 --> 00:17:52,519
But in reality,

346
00:17:54,279 --> 00:17:56,000
he had an extreme need for control

347
00:17:56,000 --> 00:17:57,200
and a twisted sense of possessiveness.

348
00:17:58,599 --> 00:18:00,759
He forbade his wife to talk to strangers,

349
00:18:02,759 --> 00:18:04,319
forbade her to ride in any man's car,

350
00:18:04,920 --> 00:18:06,680
and even snooped through her messages.

351
00:18:11,319 --> 00:18:12,720
His suspicion toward his wife

352
00:18:13,240 --> 00:18:15,720
slowly escalated to domestic violence.

353
00:18:16,759 --> 00:18:17,400
In the end,

354
00:18:18,400 --> 00:18:20,319
this seemingly kind man

355
00:18:20,880 --> 00:18:22,759
killed his own wife with his own hands.

356
00:18:25,599 --> 00:18:26,160
But

357
00:18:28,200 --> 00:18:30,039
what does that have to do with Mingliang?

358
00:18:31,359 --> 00:18:32,759
He couldn't be that kind of person.
